# restore
# Generated by: Claude Sonnet 4.6
#
# Wrapper for kwin_restore.py that presents two startup confirmation dialogs
# via kdialog before handing off to the Python script.
#
# Usage:
#   restore [kwin_restore.py options...]
#
# Recommended shell alias:
#   alias restore="$HOME/.bnt/wayland-desktop/restore"
#
# The --dry-run flag bypasses the dialogs entirely so dry runs can be
# invoked without any interaction.
#
# User hook scripts (both optional, located in user_scripts_folder from
# config.yaml; default: "./" = the project root):
#
#   restore-user-before
#       Run before kwin_restore.py.  Use it to start any background apps
#       (VPNs, SSH agents, servers) that kwin_restore.py will need running.
#       The getconfig / secret-service wrappers are available inside this
#       script.
#
#   restore-user-after
#       Run after kwin_restore.py, regardless of whether it succeeded or
#       failed (the exit code of kwin_restore.py is captured and re-applied
#       after this hook returns).  Use it for post-restore tasks such as
#       opening a terminal, triggering notifications, or cleaning up
#       temporary files created by restore-user-before.
